The paper discusses the discovery of influential entities in online social networks, which falls under the category of social influence analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the role of semantics in modeling OSN information, which falls under the categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the flow dynamics of influential content, which could fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Finally, the paper discusses the properties and applications of online social influence metrics, which could fall under the category of social computing (cs.SOC).
